In this setting, for every orientation during rotation the total magnetic flux passing though MNPP'N'M' is tthe same as through MPP'M', which has area $S=\sqrt{2} L^{2}$.
The magnetic flux is:

$$
\Phi(t)=B S \sin (\omega t)=\sqrt{2} B L^{2} \sin (\omega t) .
\tag{3}
$$

The emf running around the wire-frame is:

$$
E(t)=\frac{d}{d t} \Phi(t)=\sqrt{2} B L^{2} \omega \cos (\omega t)
\tag{4}
